24: ## 1. Astro 5.x Mental Model <a name="astro-mental-model"></a>
25: 
26: Astro is a **static-first** framework. The default behavior is to ship **zero JavaScript** to the browser. Components render to HTML at build time, and only the parts you explicitly mark as interactive ("islands") get hydrated with JavaScript.
27: 
28: ### Core Principles
29: 
30: 1. **Server-first**: Components run on the server by default. No JS shipped unless you opt in.
31: 2. **Islands**: Interactive components are "islands" of JavaScript in a "sea" of static HTML.
32: 3. **Framework-agnostic**: Use React, Vue, Svelte, or Solid — even mix them on the same page.
33: 4. **Partial hydration**: Only load JS for the components that need it, when they need it.
34: 
35: ### How It Differs from Next.js/Vite
36: 
37: | Feature | Astro | Next.js | Vite (React) |
38: |---------|-------|---------|-------------|
39: | Default JS | Zero | Full bundle | Full bundle |
40: | Rendering | Static HTML | SSR + Hydration | CSR |
41: | Interactivity | Opt-in (islands) | Opt-out (`use server`) | Always on |
42: | Routing | File-based | File-based | Manual (react-router) |
43: | Best for | Content sites, portfolios | Web apps | SPAs |
44: 
45: ### File Structure
46: 
47: ```
48: portfolio/
49: ├── public/               # Static assets (served as-is)
50: │   ├── fonts/
51: │   └── images/
52: ├── src/
53: │   ├── components/       # Reusable components
54: │   │   ├── LaptopShell.astro    # Static shell (no JS)
55: │   │   └── Terminal.tsx          # Interactive island (React)
56: │   ├── layouts/
57: │   │   └── Layout.astro         # Base HTML layout
58: │   ├── pages/
59: │   │   └── index.astro          # Routes (file = URL)
60: │   └── styles/
61: │       ├── global.css           # Design tokens + resets
62: │       ├── laptop.css           # ThinkPad styling
63: │       ├── terminal.css         # Terminal emulator
64: │       └── crt.css              # CRT scanline effects
65: ├── astro.config.mjs
66: ├── package.json
67: └── tsconfig.json
68: ```
