132: ## 3. React Islands — Client Directives <a name="react-islands"></a>
133: 
134: ### Setting Up React in Astro
135: 
136: ```bash
137: # Add React integration
138: npx astro add react
139: ```
140: 
141: This updates `astro.config.mjs`:
142: 
143: ```javascript
144: // astro.config.mjs
145: import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
146: import react from '@astrojs/react';
147: 
148: export default defineConfig({
149:   integrations: [react()],
150: });
151: ```
152: 
153: ### `client:load` — Immediate Hydration
154: 
155: ```astro
156: ---
157: import Counter from '../components/Counter.tsx';
158: ---
159: 
160: <!-- Renders on server, then hydrates on client -->
161: <Counter client:load initialCount={0} />
162: ```
163: 
164: ```tsx
165: // src/components/Counter.tsx
166: import { useState } from 'react';
167: 
168: interface CounterProps {
169:   initialCount: number;
170: }
171: 
172: export default function Counter({ initialCount }: CounterProps) {
173:   const [count, setCount] = useState(initialCount);
174:   
175:   return (
176:     <div className="counter">
177:       <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c - 1)}>-</button>
178:       <span>{count}</span>
179:       <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>+</button>
180:     </div>
181:   );
182: }
183: ```
184: 
185: ### `client:only="react"` — No SSR
186: 
187: **Use this when the component uses browser-only APIs** (window, document, navigator, or libraries like xterm.js that can't run on the server).
188: 
189: ```astro
190: ---
191: import Terminal from '../components/Terminal.tsx';
192: ---
193: 
194: <!-- Does NOT render on server. Only renders in browser. -->
195: <Terminal client:only="react" />
196: ```
197: 
198: > **⚠️ Key difference:** `client:load` renders HTML on the server first, then hydrates. `client:only` renders nothing on the server — the component only exists in the browser. You'll see a blank space during initial page load.
199: 
200: ### When to Use `client:only="react"`
201: 
202: - **xterm.js** — Requires DOM APIs, can't SSR
203: - **Canvas/WebGL** — Browser rendering context
204: - **Web Audio API** — Browser-only
205: - **localStorage/sessionStorage** — Not available on server
206: - **window.matchMedia** — No window on server
207: - **Third-party widgets** that assume browser environment
208: 
