557: ## 6. 3D CSS Transforms — Laptop Lid Animation <a name="3d-transforms"></a>
558: 
559: The portfolio features a 3D laptop that opens to reveal the terminal screen.
560: 
561: ### The Geometry
562: 
563: ```
564:          Lid (closed)
565:         ┌──────────────┐  ← rotateX(90deg) = closed
566:         │              │
567:         │   Screen     │  ← rotateX(0deg) = open
568:         │              │
569:         └──────────────┘  ← Hinge point (transform-origin: bottom)
570:         ┌──────────────┐
571:         │   Keyboard   │  ← Base (stationary)
572:         │              │
573:         └──────────────┘
574: ```
575: 
576: ### CSS Implementation
577: 
578: ```css
579: /* src/styles/laptop.css */
580: 
581: .laptop-container {
582:   /* Enable 3D space for children */
583:   perspective: 1200px;
584:   perspective-origin: 50% 50%;
585:   
586:   display: flex;
587:   flex-direction: column;
588:   align-items: center;
589:   margin: var(--space-8) auto;
590:   max-width: 900px;
591: }
592: 
593: .laptop-lid {
594:   /* The lid rotates around its bottom edge */
595:   transform-origin: bottom center;
596:   transform: rotateX(0deg);  /* 0 = open, 90 = closed */
597:   transition: transform 1.2s cubic-bezier(0.23, 1, 0.32, 1);
598:   
599:   /* Preserve 3D transforms for children */
600:   transform-style: preserve-3d;
601:   
602:   width: 100%;
603:   position: relative;
604: }
605: 
606: /* Closed state */
607: .laptop-lid.closed {
608:   transform: rotateX(85deg);  /* Not quite 90° to show a sliver */
609: }
610: 
611: /* Opening animation */
612: .laptop-lid.opening {
613:   animation: lid-open 1.5s cubic-bezier(0.23, 1, 0.32, 1) forwards;
614: }
615: 
616: @keyframes lid-open {
617:   0% {
618:     transform: rotateX(85deg);
619:   }
620:   60% {
621:     transform: rotateX(-5deg);  /* Slight overshoot */
622:   }
623:   80% {
624:     transform: rotateX(3deg);   /* Bounce back */
625:   }
626:   100% {
627:     transform: rotateX(0deg);   /* Settle */
628:   }
629: }
630: 
631: .laptop-screen {
632:   background: var(--color-bg-primary);
633:   border: 3px solid var(--thinkpad-dark-gray);
634:   border-radius: var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0 0;
635:   padding: var(--space-2);
636:   aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
637:   overflow: hidden;
638:   position: relative;
