1195: ## 11. Gotchas & Lessons Learned <a name="gotchas"></a>
1196: 
1197: ### 🚨 Gotcha #1: xterm.js Addon Imports Must Be Dynamic
1198: 
1199: **Problem:** Static imports of xterm.js and its addons crash during Astro's build step because they reference `window` and `document`.
1200: 
1201: **Before (broken):**
1202: ```tsx
1203: // ❌ This crashes during `npm run build`
1204: import { Terminal } from 'xterm';
1205: import { FitAddon } from '@xterm/addon-fit';
1206: import 'xterm/css/xterm.css';
1207: 
1208: export default function Terminal() {
1209:   // ...
1210: }
1211: ```
1212: 
1213: **After (working):**
1214: ```tsx
1215: // ✅ Dynamic imports inside useEffect — only runs in browser
1216: export default function Terminal() {
1217:   useEffect(() => {
1218:     async function init() {
1219:       const { Terminal } = await import('xterm');
1220:       const { FitAddon } = await import('@xterm/addon-fit');
1221:       await import('xterm/css/xterm.css');
1222:       
1223:       // Now safe to use Terminal, FitAddon
1224:     }
1225:     init();
1226:   }, []);
1227: }
1228: ```
1229: 
1230: And you **must** use `client:only="react"` in the Astro template — not `client:load`. The latter tries to SSR the component first, which still crashes.
1231: 
1232: ### 🚨 Gotcha #2: CRT Effects Need Careful Z-Index Management
1233: 
1234: **Problem:** CRT scanlines and flicker effects overlay the terminal. If z-index isn't managed carefully:
1235: - Scanlines block mouse clicks on the terminal
1236: - Text selection doesn't work
1237: - Cursor appears behind the overlay
1238: 
1239: **Solution — Layering order:**
1240: 
1241: ```css
1242: .screen-content {
1243:   position: relative;
1244:   z-index: var(--z-base);  /* 0 — Terminal content */
1245: }
1246: 
1247: .crt-overlay {
1248:   position: absolute;
1249:   top: 0;
1250:   left: 0;
1251:   right: 0;
1252:   bottom: 0;
1253:   z-index: var(--z-scanlines);  /* 200 — Above content */
1254:   pointer-events: none;  /* ⚠️ CRITICAL: Allow clicks to pass through */
1255: }
1256: 
1257: .scanlines {
1258:   position: absolute;
1259:   top: 0;
1260:   left: 0;
1261:   right: 0;
1262:   bottom: 0;
1263:   background: repeating-linear-gradient(
1264:     0deg,
1265:     rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15) 0px,
1266:     rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15) 1px,
1267:     transparent 1px,
1268:     transparent 3px
1269:   );
1270:   pointer-events: none;
1271: }
1272: 
1273: .crt-flicker {
1274:   position: absolute;
1275:   top: 0;
1276:   left: 0;
1277:   right: 0;
1278:   bottom: 0;
1279:   background: rgba(0, 255, 65, 0.02);
1280:   animation: flicker 0.1s infinite alternate;
1281:   pointer-events: none;
1282: }
1283: 
1284: @keyframes flicker {
1285:   from { opacity: 0.95; }
1286:   to { opacity: 1.0; }
1287: }
1288: ```
1289: 
1290: > **The key rule:** Any overlay element that's purely visual MUST have `pointer-events: none`. Without it, users can't interact with the terminal below.
1291: 
1292: ### 🚨 Gotcha #3: Astro Scoped Styles Don't Reach React Islands
1293: 
1294: **Problem:** Styles defined in `<style>` tags in `.astro` files are scoped. They won't apply to children rendered by React islands.
1295: 
1296: **Solution:** Use `:global()` or import CSS from the React component:
1297: 
1298: ```astro
1299: <style>
1300:   /* This WON'T style the Terminal component's internals */
1301:   .terminal-container { color: green; }
1302:   
1303:   /* This WILL */
1304:   :global(.terminal-container) { color: green; }
1305: </style>
1306: ```
1307: 
1308: Or better — use a separate CSS file imported in the React component:
1309: ```tsx
1310: // Terminal.tsx
1311: import '../styles/terminal.css';  // Imported in the component itself
1312: ```
1313: 
1314: ### 🚨 Gotcha #4: Font Loading Delays
1315: 
1316: **Problem:** Custom fonts (IBM Plex Mono) take time to load. The terminal briefly shows in the fallback font, then shifts when the custom font loads (FOUT — Flash of Unstyled Text).
1317: 
1318: **Solution:** Preload the font:
1319: ```html
1320: <head>
1321:   <link rel="preload" href="/fonts/IBMPlexMono-Regular.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin />
1322:   <link rel="preload" href="/fonts/IBMPlexMono-Bold.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin />
1323: </head>
1324: ```
1325: 
1326: Or use `font-display: swap` in your `@font-face`:
1327: ```css
1328: @font-face {
1329:   font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono';
1330:   src: url('/fonts/IBMPlexMono-Regular.woff2') format('woff2');
1331:   font-weight: 400;
1332:   font-display: swap;
1333: }
1334: ```
